<paragraph blockId="13.[816,1475,1357,2053]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[816,1106,1612,1637]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Carapace and mesosoma</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1124,1256,1613,1637]" captionStart="Figures 54–55" captionStartId="16.[116,193,2016,2038]" captionTargetBox="[112,1473,234,2001]" captionTargetId="figure-40@16.[112,1473,234,2003]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figures 54–55. Chaerilus pulcherrimus sp. n., holotYpe male, carapace and tergites (54), and sternopectinal region and sternites (55)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4648908" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4648908/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Figs. 54–55</figureCitation>
). Carapace covered bY large granules in both sexes; anterior margin of carapace almost straight; two well developed pairs of lateral eYes and one pair of median eYes present; mesosomal tergites irregularlY granulated, mainlY on tergite VII; all sternites smooth without carinae and granulation; sternite V with smooth patch indicated; pectinal tooth count 
<specimenCount box="[1296,1316,1805,1828]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
4, 
<specimenCount box="[1350,1370,1805,1828]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
