<paragraph blockId="14.[113,772,1310,2038]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,224,1310,1334]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Pedipalps</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[246,380,1310,1334]" captionStart-0="Figures 63–71" captionStart-1="Figures 72–79" captionStartId-0="18.[112,189,1990,2012]" captionStartId-1="19.[117,194,1969,1991]" captionTargetBox-0="[125,1451,229,1977]" captionTargetBox-1="[141,1445,240,1948]" captionTargetId-0="figure-72@18.[113,1474,225,1987]" captionTargetId-1="figure-52@19.[113,1474,226,1958]" captionTargetPageId-0="18" captionTargetPageId-1="19" captionText-0="Figures 63–71. Chaerilus pulcherrimus sp. n., holotYpe male, pedipalp chela, dorsal (63), externodorsal (64), and ventrointernal (65) views. Pedipalp patella, dorsal (66), external (67) and ventral (68) views. Pedipalp femur and trochanter, dorsalointernal (69) and ventral (70) views. Movable finger (71) dentition. The trichobothrial pattern is indicated in Figures 63–69." captionText-1="Figures 72–79. Chaerilus pulcherrimus sp. n., paratYpe female, pedipalp chela, dorsal (72), external (73), and ventral (74) views. Pedipalp patella, dorsal (75), external (76) and ventral (77) views. Pedipalp femur and trochanter, dorsalointernal (78) view. Movable finger (79) dentition." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4648914" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4648916" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/4648914/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/4648916/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Figs. 63–79</figureCitation>
). Pedipalp chela rather stout with swollen manus mainlY in female; movable finger with 8 and fixed finger with 7 imbricated rows of granules; chela with 7 carinae, smooth in both sexes; dorsal and internal surfaces of chela with reticulate granulation patterns; patella with 4–5 smooth, reduced carinae, or carinae absent; surfaces of patella smooth except for internal surface which is sparselY granulated; femur denselY granulated with four incomplete carinae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[113,772,1310,2038]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,166,1598,1622]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Legs</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[180,306,1598,1622]" captionStart="Figures 56–62" captionStartId="17.[113,190,2010,2032]" captionTargetBox="[128,1463,226,1989]" captionTargetId="figure-57@17.[113,1474,223,2000]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figures 56–62: Chaerilus pulcherrimus sp. n. Figure 56. ParatYpe female, telson lateral. Figures 57–62. HolotYpe male, telson lateral (57), metasoma and telson, lateral (58), dorsal (59), and ventral (60) views, left legs III–IV, retrolateral aspect (61–62). Scale bar: 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4648910" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4648910/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Figs. 61–62</figureCitation>
). Hirsute, without bristlecombs and carinae; femora and patellae smooth; tarsomeres with two rows of spiniform setae; spiniform seta formula 5–6/5–7: 6–7/6–7: 7–8/7–8: 7–8/7–9.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[113,772,1310,2038]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,348,1726,1750]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Hemispermatophore</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[365,498,1726,1750]" captionStart="Figures 80–83" captionStartId="20.[115,192,1395,1417]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,279,1335]" captionTargetId="figure-71@20.[113,1474,259,1360]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figures 80–83. Chaerilus pulcherrimus sp. n., left hemispermatophore. Figures 80–83. Whole hemispermatophore in posterior (80), convex (81) and anterior (82) views. Figure 83. Capsule and distal lamina, convex view (compressed), fine refractile structure visualized under Nomarksi illumination. Scale bars: 400 μm (80–81, 82), 200 μm (83)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4648919" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4648919/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Figs. 80–83</figureCitation>
). Fusiform; distal lamina short, broad, weaklY tapered, apex rounded; capsule with distal carina weaklY sclerotized; sperm hemiduct delineated bY two thin, sclerotized carinae, of which the distal is longer, the basal shorter; capsule elongate, ca. 50% longer than distal lamina; trunk long, as broad as capsule. Measurements of left hemispermatophore (mm): distal lamina length 0.35, capsule length 0.53, trunk length 1.10, pedicel length 0.22, capsule width 0.30. Right hemispermatophore similar to the left hemispermatophore.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[816,1475,1310,1462]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[816,937,1310,1334]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Karyotype</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[963,1104,1310,1334]" captionStart="Figures 84–86" captionStartId="20.[113,190,1981,2003]" captionTargetBox="[125,1476,1510,1959]" captionTargetId="figure-72@20.[115,1476,1510,1959]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figures 84–86: The chromosomes of Chaerilus species. Figure 84. C. kautti sp. n., meiotic metaphase I. Figures 85–86. C. pulcherrimus sp. n., mitotic metaphase (85) and meiotic metaphase I (86). Scale bar: 10 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4648922" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4648922/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Figs. 85–86</figureCitation>
). Male 
<typeStatus box="[1204,1297,1310,1334]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">holotYpe</typeStatus>
was analYzed. The diploid complement is 102 chromosomes in the mitotic metaphases (
<figureCitation box="[955,1036,1374,1398]" captionStart="Figures 84–86" captionStartId="20.[113,190,1981,2003]" captionTargetBox="[125,1476,1510,1959]" captionTargetId="figure-72@20.[115,1476,1510,1959]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figures 84–86: The chromosomes of Chaerilus species. Figure 84. C. kautti sp. n., meiotic metaphase I. Figures 85–86. C. pulcherrimus sp. n., mitotic metaphase (85) and meiotic metaphase I (86). Scale bar: 10 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4648922" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4648922/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Fig. 85</figureCitation>
). During metaphase I, 51 bivalents were observed (
<figureCitation box="[926,1004,1406,1430]" captionStart="Figures 84–86" captionStartId="20.[113,190,1981,2003]" captionTargetBox="[125,1476,1510,1959]" captionTargetId="figure-72@20.[115,1476,1510,1959]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figures 84–86: The chromosomes of Chaerilus species. Figure 84. C. kautti sp. n., meiotic metaphase I. Figures 85–86. C. pulcherrimus sp. n., mitotic metaphase (85) and meiotic metaphase I (86). Scale bar: 10 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4648922" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4648922/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Fig. 86</figureCitation>
), implYing that 2n=102. Chiasmata were not observed during meiosis.
</paragraph>
